 called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":39,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705202,"age":48,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705206,"age":61,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705207,"age":75,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705212,"age":110,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Pratt was born in 1510, in England. He married Margaret in 1530, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1510–":"1510–Surnud","1513–Female":"1513–Surnud","1540–Male":"1540–Surnud","1510–Male":"1510–Surnud","1558":"1558","1513":"1513","1510":"1510","1620":"1620","1530":"1530","1585":"1585","1540":"1540","1571":"1571","1549":"1549","England":"England"},"fi":{"1510–":"1510–Kuollut","1513–Female":"1513–Kuollut","1540–Male":"1540–Kuollut","1510–Male":"1510–Kuollut","1558":"1558","1513":"1513","1510":"1510","1620":"1620","1530":"1530","1585":"1585","1540":"1540","1571":"1571","1549":"1549","England":"England"},"fr":{"1510–":"1510–Décédé","1513–Female":"1513–Décédée","1540–Male":"1540–Décédé","1510–Male":"1510–Décédé","1558":"1558","1513":"1513","1510":"1510","1620":"1620","1530":"1530","1585":"1585","1540":"1540","1571":"1571","1549":"1549","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Thomas Pratt est né en 1510, à Angleterre. Il a épousé Margaret en 1530, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1510–":"1510–Verstorben","1513–Female":"1513–Verstorben","1540–Male":"1540–Verstorben","1510–Male":"1510–Verstorben","1558":"1558","1513":"1513","1510":"1510","1620":"1620","1530":"1530","1585":"1585","1540":"1540","1571":"1571","1549":"1549","England":"England","lifeSummary":"Thomas Pratt wurde 1510 in England geboren. Er hat 1530 in England Margaret geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1510–":